rect.title: Work done (by external forces e.g frictional force, applied force) = change in energy (e.g. KE, GPE, EPE) of system
Work done by a force is the product of the force and the displacement in the direction of the force.
Work done by an external agent in stretching a spring within the proportionality limit
Work done by a gas expanding against a constant external pressure
Energy is never created nor destroyed; may be transferred / converted from one form to another. Total energy of an isolated system remains constant
